  "prompt": "What are the views of the young generation on feminism in India?",
  "response": "The views of young Indians on feminism are diverse and evolving. Here are some general observations:\n\n1. Urban Perspectives:\n- More supportive of gender equality\n- Advocate for women's rights and opportunities\n- Challenge traditional patriarchal norms\n- Strong presence on social media platforms\n\n2. Progressive Views:\n- Support equal education and career opportunities\n- Demand workplace gender equality\n- Challenge sexual harassment and discrimination\n- Advocate for reproductive rights\n\n3. Intersectional Approach:\n- Recognize diversity within feminist movements\n- Consider issues of caste, class, and religion\n- Support marginalized women's rights\n\n4. Conservative Perspectives:\n- Some view feminism as Western import\n- Believe in traditional gender roles\n- Skeptical of radical feminist approaches\n\n5. Digital Activism:\n- Use social media for awareness\n- Support #MeToo and similar movements\n- Share personal experiences of gender discrimination\n\n6. Challenges:\n- Resistance from conservative social structures\n- Cultural and familial pressures\n- Uneven implementation of gender equality laws\n\nNote: These views are generalized and can vary significantly based on individual experiences, education, region, and socio-economic background.",
